This kind of extreme distribution might not be seen as a good compromise because one group is significantly disadvantaged compared to the others in each proposal.

Proposal one, meanwhile, delivers maximum benefit to group cow-🐮, the same as in proposal two, but doesn't disadvantage group apple-🍎 or group bee-🐝 as much as proposals two and three do. All groups get an increased lifespan, although it's true that group cow-🐮 gets a significantly larger benefit.

It might not be a perfect compromise, but given these options, proposal one appears to be the best compromise because it doesn't drastically disadvantage any group as much as proposals two and three.
